reviews_data.review_text:
The concept of this place is nice, but the execution is terrible. The staff is one of the worst I’ve encountered. Mostly teenagers who clearly aren’t trained and don’t know what they’re doing. The place isn’t very sanitary either. I saw multiple flies in the cases, and they’re practically out of everything before 5 PM.

When I asked for my pastry to be heated up, the employee left it in so long that the frosting completely melted off the donut. I was going to complain, but they’d already given me attitude when I ordered a pumpkin drink. On top of that, they don’t even ask about rewards and actually made me pay for an extra bag of chips just to use the app for a free pastry. Also there’s no reason a donut should be $10. And a disgusting coffee $8?? That’s more than Starbucks.

The staff always looks “busy” but the line moves incredibly slow. The drinks are mediocre at best the coffee is awful, and it’s clear no one is trained properly. To make it worse, employees have their hair down and don’t wear gloves while handling pastries, which is just gross.

This place is completely overhyped and not worth going out of your way for. If you want something similar with far better service and quality, I recommend Tous Les Jours. I definitely won’t be returning
